Floyd Mayweather Jnr and Manny Pacquiao met for over an hour on Tuesday night in a bid to hammer out the details of their proposed $300million (£200m) mega-fight.

Mayweather visited Pacquiao in his Miami hotel suite for what was described as a 'very pleasant and very encouraging' discussion.

The pair had earlier sat on opposite sides of a basketball court as Miami Heat took on the Milwaukee Bucks in the NBA.

