They talked briefly at half-time and exchanged phone numbers during what was their first ever face-to-face conversation.

The fight has been in the works for almost six years but appears close to being agreed for the MGM Grand in Las Vegas on May 2.

'That's the first time they ever sat eye to eye,' Pacquiao's adviser Michael Konz told ESPN.

'They talked at half-time, but this was a longer, more serious meeting. You could tell by their body language that this was very positive. It was for a good hour or more.

